OL,3,CAround 6% of UK adults diagnosed with
OL,4,Cfood allergies, study reveals
OL,6,FAround 2.4 million adults living in
OL,7,Fthe UK have been diagnosed with a food
OL,8,Fallergy by a doctor, according to a
OL,9,Fstudy by the food safety watchdog.
OL,11,FMore than 30% of adults said they have
OL,12,Fsymptoms of food 'hypersensitivity',
OL,13,Fincluding allergies, intolerances and
OL,14,Fcoeliac disease, meaning they have an
OL,15,Funpleasant reaction to certain foods.
OL,17,FThe research also found that when
OL,18,Fpeople had multiple food allergies, it
OL,19,Fwas often associated with an allergy
OL,20,Fto tree pollen, like birch.
