OL,3,CAround 6% of UK adults diagnosed with
OL,4,Cfood allergies, study reveals
OL,6,FThe study by the Food Standards
OL,7,FAgency's (FSA) Patterns and Prevalence
OL,8,Fof Adult Food Allergy (PAFA) found
OL,9,Fthat foods such as peanuts, hazelnuts,
OL,10,Fwalnuts and almonds are the most
OL,11,Flikely to cause an allergic reaction
OL,13,FPeople also reported allergies to
OL,14,Ffruits, such as apple, peach and kiwi.
OL,16,FBut the report concluded that
OL,17,Fallergies to milk, fish, shrimp and
OL,18,Fmussels were uncommon.
