OL,3,CAround 6% of UK adults diagnosed with
OL,4,Cfood allergies, study reveals
OL,6,FMost adults living with food allergies
OL,7,Fdeveloped them in childhood, but 70%
OL,8,Fsaid their allergies started when they
OL,9,Fwere an adult.
OL,11,FDespite the findings, the report said
OL,12,Ffurther evidence is needed to
OL,13,Funderstand how environmental factors,
OL,14,Fincluding pollution, climate change
OL,15,Fand highly urbanised environments, and
OL,16,Fexposure to birch and related tree
OL,17,Fpollens, lead to adult-onset food
OL,18,Fallergies.
