OL,3,CAround 6% of UK adults diagnosed with
OL,4,Cfood allergies, study reveals
OL,6,F"These new FSA figures show at least
OL,7,F6% of adults in the UK now have a
OL,8,Fdiagnosed food allergy. This equates
OL,9,Fto a staggering 2.4 million adults
OL,10,Fliving with a diagnosed food allergy
OL,11,Fin this country. These figures do not
OL,12,Ftake into account children, who
OL,13,Fgenerally have twice the rate of food
OL,14,Fallergy compared with adults.
