OL,3,CAround 6% of UK adults diagnosed with
OL,4,Cfood allergies, study reveals
OL,6,F"Through this research, we can see
OL,7,Fpatterns such as the emergence of
OL,8,Fplant-based allergies affecting more
OL,9,Fpeople into adulthood, which is
OL,10,Fimportant for us to consider as we've
OL,11,Fseen the food system move towards
OL,12,Fplant-based diets and alternative
OL,13,Fproteins.
OL,15,F"The FSA remains committed to ensuring
OL,16,Fthat consumers have clear and accurate
OL,17,Fallergen labelling to support people
OL,18,Fin the UK living with a food allergy.
